The course provides an overview of methods and principles of anesthesia, preparation for anesthesia and treatment after anesthesia. In terms of emergency medicine, the main attention is paid to the critically ill patient. Treatment algorithms for critical situations that occur in the dentist's practice - airway obstruction, anaphylactic shock, cardiac arrest - are discussed. Practical resuscitation training, life-threatening cardiac arrhythmias and their treatment principles are learned.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course covers diagnosis and treatment of critical conditions, resuscitation, principles of the airway management and anesthesia and monitoring of the patient during anesthesia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Diagnosis and treatment of most frequent life-threatening conditions. 
Knowing ERC 2021 guidelines and perfoming cardiopulmonary resuscitation. 
Knowledge of anesthesia methods and patient monitoring in the perioperative period. Airway management at the level required by a general practitioner.
